<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="https://jamienoel.com/xml/base.min.xml"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Programming on JH Noel</title><link>https://jamienoel.com/tags/programming/</link><description>Recent content in Programming on JH Noel</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 06:46:27 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://jamienoel.com/tags/programming/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Welcome</title><link>https://jamienoel.com/posts/welcome/</link><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 06:46:27 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jamienoel.com/posts/welcome/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is my personal site, built with &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/"&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; and hosted on GitHub Pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I use this space to write about mathematics, programming, and other topics that interest me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The site supports &lt;strong&gt;LaTeX math rendering&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Euler&amp;rsquo;s identity: 
&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;π&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt; e^{i\pi} + 1 = 0 &lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And display equations:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msubsup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∫&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;∞&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;∞&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msubsup&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msqrt&gt;&lt;mi&gt;π&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msqrt&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;
\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^2} dx = \sqrt{\pi}
&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description></item><item><title>Notes on Gradient Descent</title><link>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-ml/</link><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-ml/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A brief exploration of optimization in high-dimensional spaces.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2 id="the-basic-update-rule"&gt;
 &lt;a class="Heading-link u-clickable" href="https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-ml/#the-basic-update-rule"&gt;The Basic Update Rule&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gradient descent follows a simple iterative scheme:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;θ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;θ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;η&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;∇&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;θ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;J&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;θ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;
\theta_{t+1} = \theta_t - \eta \nabla_\theta J(\theta_t)
&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$\theta$ represents the model parameters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$\eta$ is the learning rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$J$ is the loss function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;




&lt;h2 id="key-considerations"&gt;
 &lt;a class="Heading-link u-clickable" href="https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-ml/#key-considerations"&gt;Key Considerations&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The choice of learning rate dramatically affects convergence.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Eigenvalues: Why They Matter</title><link>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-eigenvalues/</link><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 14:30:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-eigenvalues/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Eigenvalues and eigenvectors reveal fundamental properties of linear transformations.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2 id="definition"&gt;
 &lt;a class="Heading-link u-clickable" href="https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-eigenvalues/#definition"&gt;Definition&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A non-zero vector $\mathbf{v}$ is an eigenvector of matrix $A$ with eigenvalue $\lambda$ if:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;
A\mathbf{v} = \lambda\mathbf{v}
&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;




&lt;h2 id="applications"&gt;
 &lt;a class="Heading-link u-clickable" href="https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-eigenvalues/#applications"&gt;Applications&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stability analysis of dynamical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Principal component analysis (PCA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spectral clustering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>A Useful Python Pattern</title><link>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-code/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jamienoel.com/posts/placeholder-code/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Using context managers for clean resource management:&lt;/p&gt;

 

&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; contextlib &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; contextmanager
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;@contextmanager&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;managed_resource&lt;/span&gt;(name):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Acquiring &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;yield&lt;/span&gt; name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Releasing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; managed_resource(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;lock&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; r:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Using resource: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;r&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This ensures cleanup happens even if exceptions occur.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>